 the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]},{"name":"Mared","meanings":["Simplified form of   Marged ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margred Marlos was born about 1420, in Wales as the daughter of William Marlos. She had at least 1 daughter with Hugh Howell."},"et":{"abt 1420–":"umbes 1420–Surnud","1420–Female":"1420–Surnud","1372–Male":"1372–Surnud","1420–1450":"1420–1450","1502–Female":"1502–Surnud","1260–Female":"1260–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1502":"1502","1420":"1420","about 1502":"umbes 1502","1450":"1450","1372":"1372","1260":"1260","abt 1420":"umbes 1420","Wales":"Wales"},"fi":{"abt 1420–":"noin 1420–Kuollut","1420–Female":"1420–Kuollut","1372–Male":"1372–Kuollut","1420–1450":"1420–1450","1502–Female":"1502–Kuollut","1260–Female":"1260–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1502":"1502","1420":"1420","about 1502":"noin 1502","1450":"1450","1372":"1372","1260":"1260","abt 1420":"noin 1420","Wales":"Wales"},"fr":{"abt 1420–":"environ 1420–Décédée","1420–Female":"1420–Décédée","1372–Male":"1372–Décédé","1420–1450":"1420–1450","1502–Female":"1502–Décédée","1260–Female":"1260–Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1502":"1502","1420":"1420","about 1502":"environ 1502","1450":"1450","1372":"1372","1260":"1260","abt 1420":"environ 1420","Wales":"Galles","lifeSummary":"Margred Marlos est née environ 1420, à Galles, fille de William Marlos. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Hugh Howell."},"de":{"abt 1420–":"um 1420–Verstorben","1420–Female":"1420–Verstorben","1372–Male